text: Interrogatories to Plaintiff
DEFINITIONS AND INSTRUCTIONS
The term "incident" refers to the trip and fall accident that occurred on January 23, 2024, at the Sierra County Fair.
The term "you" or "your" refers to the plaintiff, John Doe.
The term "document" refers to all written, printed, recorded, or graphic material, however produced or reproduced, including electronic records and emails.
INTERROGATORIES
General Information
State your full name, date of birth, current address, and any other names you have used or been known by.
Identify all addresses where you have resided for the past ten (10) years.
Circumstances of the Incident
Describe in detail the events leading up to, during, and immediately following the incident on January 23, 2024.
Identify all persons who witnessed the incident or have knowledge of the circumstances surrounding the incident, including their names, addresses, and relationship to you.
State the specific location at the Sierra County Fair where the incident occurred, and describe the conditions of the area at the time of the incident.
Cause of the Incident
Describe any obstacles, hazards, or other conditions that you believe caused or contributed to the incident.
State whether you consumed any alcohol, drugs, or medication within 24 hours prior to the incident. If so, identify the substances and the amounts consumed.
Aftermath of the Incident
Describe all injuries you sustained as a result of the incident, specifying the nature and extent of each injury.
Identify all persons who provided you with medical care or treatment for injuries related to the incident, including their names, addresses, and dates of treatment.
Describe all medical treatment you have received for injuries related to the incident, including surgeries, medications, physical therapy, and any other forms of treatment.
Prior Medical Conditions
Identify all medical conditions, injuries, or illnesses you have had in the past ten (10) years, including the names and addresses of the treating physicians or medical providers.
State whether you have ever suffered any injury to the same body parts involved in the incident. If so, describe the circumstances and treatment received.
Medical Care in Connection to the Incident

text: Provide the names and addresses of all hospitals, clinics, or medical facilities where you have received treatment for injuries related to the incident.
List all medications prescribed to you as a result of the injuries from the incident, including the name, dosage, and prescribing physician.
Identify any medical tests, examinations, or diagnostic procedures you have undergone in connection with the injuries sustained in the incident.
Prior Earnings through Present
Describe your employment history for the past five (5) years, including the names and addresses of employers, job titles, duties, and dates of employment.
State your average monthly earnings for each year from 2019 to the present, including bonuses, commissions, and other forms of compensation.
Describe any loss of earnings or earning capacity you claim to have suffered as a result of the incident.
Current Medical Status
Describe your current medical condition, including any ongoing symptoms or limitations resulting from the injuries sustained in the incident.
Identify all healthcare providers you are currently seeing for the injuries related to the incident, including their names, addresses, and the nature of the treatment.
Describe any future medical treatment you anticipate needing as a result of the injuries sustained in the incident.
Vocational Training and Abilities
Describe any vocational training, education, or certifications you have received.
State whether you have participated in any vocational rehabilitation or job retraining programs since the incident. If so, provide details of the programs.
Impact of the Incident
Describe any limitations or restrictions on your daily activities as a result of the injuries sustained in the incident.
Identify all claims for damages you are making as a result of the incident, including general damages, special damages, and any other forms of relief sought.
